## 4. UX and pedagogy

### 4.1 Guides

- **Code Tour** explains code; **Tuning Guide** runs tuning workflow. Never merge.
- **Socratic** — no “set to 2.5 m” buttons, no one-click correct constants.
- Aid highlights decay over steps (`aidLevel.ts`).
- Gate Next on prerequisites (teleop, live tuning, sim running) per step.

### 4.2 Templates and vendors

- Browser REV template = **SparkMax + SparkMaxConfig** — **not YAMS** (YAMS only in mantik-pid-practice).
- Robot tab = **Robot.java** (TimedRobot) — **not RobotContainer**.
- Vendor choice affects **physics motor** (NEO vs Kraken) **and** Java boilerplate.

### 4.3 UI naming

Use derivative names in the sim UI (SpringTune, BenchScope, TraceView). Keep FRC lesson links to real Elastic / AdvantageScope.

### 4.4 Layout

- Primary learning surface = mechanism + graph (BenchScope). Tuning panel = narrow strip (~24% width desktop).
- Mechanism view **always visible** — not a toggle.
- Mobile: stack panels; do not require drag/resize for Chromebook labs.

### 4.5 Reference hints

`elevatorReference.ts` (and future `*Reference.ts`) gives **ranges and hints**, not answers. Document motor choice and plant source in reference file comments.

